www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I hope..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
OR remove the caster nerf on there damage. Right now casters only do 2/3 damage with their spells.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Around the velious era it made a lot of sense to unnerf the PvP spell damage nerf...but now with the changes since Luclin that would be insane.  With critical hits, AA's, Elnerick's Electrical Rending, etc... there is just no way it would make sense to unnerf spell damage.  Most casters other than mages are pretty well balenced now in PvP.  (I'm talking at level 60 with AA's.)   The single thing that makes level 60 epic mages under balenced is the ability of bards and enchanters to poof the epic pet.  Even when I summon 2 elemental blankets, 3 daggers of symbols, and get resist magic cast on my epic pet, its only a matter of time before a bard will successfully poof it.  Of course I know not everyone has their epics, and a mage without an epic is a joke in PvP.  Hybrids and melees most of the time, don't even need to counter a non-epic pet....they just kite them around and ignore them.<br>
<br>
This is why I am so dissappointed that this changes will not effect PC's casting on pets.  In one single swoop Verant could have balenced Mages and Beatlords in PvP.  In fact, in my mind this would have been THE perfect solution which would have finally balenced these classes for PvP.  I can't speak to much for Beastlords as I have never played one, but as a mage I think this would have completely balenced the class.  We'd still be stuck with our gimpy slow casting nukes, but now our pets, which SHOULD be our major offensive ability would be a force to be dealt with.  <br>
<br>
It would have had the effect of giving a very nice boost to necromancers which are allready an incredibly powerful (if not the most powerful) PvP class, and I think most people agree that necros don't need much if any PvP balencing at this point.  (The most powerful necros on SZ readily admit that they are overpowered in PvP.)  However, most level 60 necros I see don't use their pets in PvP very often at all.  Maybe if this change had affected Pets in PvP it would encourage them to use their pets more often.  Even if level 60 necros did start using their pets more often it still wouldn't have been as large a boost to them as it would have been for Mages or Beastlords since Necros cannot SoW or Velocity their own pets,  and a pet without some sort of movement speed enhancement is pretty worthless in most PvP situations.<br>
<br>
Yes, and epic pet with velocity, and close to or over 200MR might be a &quot;bit devastating&quot; in PVP...but shouldn't it be?  Mages have the hardest epic in the game.  Given the effort that goes into obtaining teh mage epic, shouldn't mages have a devestating PvP weapon?  Does Verant apreciate how &quot;devastating&quot; a level 60 SK with 5k hp's and the ability to summon that SoC speed horse is?  Or how devestating, a wizard casting crit lure of ice's is?  Or how devestating manaburn and lifeburn are?  Or how devastating &quot;funeral Pyre&quot; can be?  What about how devastating a primal weilding warrior with 7k hp's riding on a horse is?  Yes it would be a powerful weapon for the mage, but it would not overpower us.  It would only bring us inline with where the other devestating classes are at this point, and it would still cost us a lot more work to get there.<br>
<br>
EDIT: BTW, I know SOE said  &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> We didn't want to make a change that would probably be more than a bit devastating in PvP without having more information.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;, which implies that they may implement this change or other changes later on for PvP.   No one on a PvP server believes that SOE will address Mage PvP balence issues at a later time.  Those of you who play on blue servers might not be able to apreciate just how much of a lack of credibility SOE has with the PvP community at this point in time, but that IS the situations as it stands. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uforyst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Foryst</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/21/02 7:32:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utarqal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarqal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(7/21/02 9:11:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=579.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  pet resistances</span><hr size=1> I haven't posted here much, and y'all are gonna think I am nuts... such as life...<br>
<br>
I think pet resistances are fine as they are. Remember, this is a PET we are talking about, not some kind of avatar. A 60 shaman can slow and root your pet? So? It is enough right now that my pet outdamages 99 percent of the level 60 warriors i play with. He outdamages every ranger, every paladin, and almost all the shadowknights. I can solo the north and west halls of howling stones, and with a 60 cleric, can pull and keep the spawn down on south hall. Is it such a bad thing that end game mobs like level 70 dragons can cause my pet such magic based damage? Also, how cheap will it be when we buff the hell out of the mage controlling a pet, put him out of AE dispell range, and let the pet sit there and tank away, whilst all the real tanks are dispelled and need to use strategy to maintain their buffs for resistances. I know this would be nice for us, but, already people are complaining about mage pets being overly tough. I think this resistance change makes them even more tough, and will draw enough attention to get us nerfed down the road.  Are we truly gimped by having a pet with level 49 resist rates that we can chain cast and not care if it dies? In the case of the epic, are we gimped because he quads for 77 against a fearing dragon for 3 mins while we make him fearless? Is this really something we NEED? Is this just gravy?<br>
<br>
I am sorry to be the single dissenting opinion here, but our class rocks, folks. I love my mage, and I think we are balanced, powerful, great at soloing, great in groups, great for farming.... Sheesh, I have a tough time finding thigs we can't do...<br>
<br>
Tarqal Evermore<br>
