<br>
As for resistances, I dueled my pet with a cleric the other, day. Yes, clerics suck in duels, but, they have a quick casting root spell.  <br>
<br>
Level 60 cleric vs Ubober, the cleric had &quot;immobilize&quot; resisted 17 of 19 times in a fight. With 130 Resistance, the cleric was being nuked a LOT for about 120 or so points of damage. Of course the cleric got waxed, but the point of the duel was to contest that pets dont resist for crap. Maybe the epic has just a good resist to magic based root. <br>
<br>
Again, i'm not a programmer, I am simply going off of my experience. My pet seems to resist things quite well, but I need more concrete analysis than this. If anyone else is good with parsers, please post some comparisons of pet damage vs some of these other classes. End game mobs, XP groups.. whatever you feel is most appropriate. I would like some concrete analysis before I crystalize this theory in my own mind. <br>
<br>
I appreciate the comments thus far, I am not one to stick to an opinion if it is wrong, so lets get some hard factual data. I've been playin this game, off and on, since 2 days after it came out. I love my mage, but I surely don't want to get him buffed all to hell so someone can nerf my poor little elemental despite me. :P<br>
